data.enText: an object, a tradition, etc. that has survived from a period of time that no longer exists

data.chText: 这座建筑物是小镇棉纺业仅存的遗迹。
data.enText: The building stands as the last remaining relic of the town's cotton industry.
a part of the body or clothing of a holy person, or sth that they owned, that is kept after their death and respected as a religious object

tr: an antiquity that has survived from the distant past

value.def: If you refer to something or someone as a relic of an earlier period, you mean that they belonged to that period but have survived into the present.

example.ex: The tower is a relic of grim days when big houses had to be fortified against invaders...
example.tran: 这座塔是那些灰暗岁月的遗迹，那时大房子不得不被加固,以抵御侵略者。

example.ex: Germany's asylum law is a relic of an era in European history which has passed...
example.tran: 德国的收容法是欧洲历史上一个已逝去时期的遗留产物。

example.ex: He found himself thinking of the man as a relic from the past.
example.tran: 他把这个男人看成是过去时代的人物。

value.def: A relic is something which was made or used a long time ago and which is kept for its historical significance.
value.tran: (有历史价值的)遗物，遗迹，遗址

value.def: A relic is the body of a saint or something else associated with a saint, which some people regard as holy.
